                <h2>Rotation</h2>
                <ol class="rotation-steps">
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Activate Both Auras</strong> -- Keep Fanaticism Aura (Crit + Attack Speed) and Defiance Aura (Armor + Resistances + Unstoppable) active permanently. These are your core offensive and defensive buffers. Without both active, the build feels weak and squishy.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Build Fanaticism Stacks with Punish</strong> -- Use Punish to quickly ramp Fanaticism Aura stacks before engaging packs. Each stack increases Crit Chance and Attack Speed. Reach max stacks before diving into combat for optimal burst damage.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Falling Star into pack centers</strong> -- Use Falling Star to gap close into the center of enemy groups. The invulnerability frames during the dash let you position safely. Aim to land surrounded by as many enemies as possible for maximum mark coverage.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Cast Judgment immediately</strong> -- As soon as you land, cast Judgment to mark and stun all nearby enemies. This is your primary burst skill. The stun freezes enemies in place, ensuring they stay grouped for chain detonations.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Wait for mark detonations</strong> -- Judgment marks detonate automatically after a short duration. When they explode, Seal of the Second Trumpet causes them to chain to additional enemies. Judgment Day passive spreads marks to unmarked enemies, creating cascading explosions.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Spam Blessed Hammer during cooldown</strong> -- While Judgment is on cooldown, cast Blessed Hammer for filler damage. The hammers spiral outward, maintaining DPS during burst windows. Keep casting until Judgment comes back up.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Reposition and repeat</strong> -- After the burst window expires, use Falling Star to reposition into new packs or escape danger. Maintain Fanaticism stacks with Punish during movement, then dive back in with Judgment when it's ready.</p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="rotation-step">
                        <p><strong>Chain detonations at critical mass</strong> -- In dense packs with high CDR, Judgment cooldown resets quickly from detonations. The build reaches critical mass where chains spawn more chains, creating screen-wide explosions that feel self-perpetuating.</p>
                    </li>
                </ol>
            </div>

            <div class="section">
                <h2>Gameplay Tips</h2>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Both auras must be active at all times.</strong>
                    <p>Fanaticism provides your Crit and Attack Speed scaling. Defiance provides your survivability. Fighting without either active is suicide. Check your buff bar regularly and recast if either drops off.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>CDR is your most important stat.</strong>
                    <p>This build is completely cooldown-dependent. Without sufficient CDR, Judgment cooldown feels punishingly long and your DPS drops dramatically. Prioritize CDR on gear until Judgment comes back up every 6-8 seconds.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Position in pack centers before casting Judgment.</strong>
                    <p>Judgment has a circular AoE around you. If you cast from the edge, you miss half the pack. Use Falling Star to dive into the center, then cast Judgment to mark everything simultaneously. Better positioning = more marks = bigger chains.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Seal of the Second Trumpet is the power spike.</strong>
                    <p>The build works without it -- Judgment alone provides solid burst damage. But the Seal of the Second Trumpet ring transforms the build from "good" to "A-Tier" by enabling screen-wide chain detonations that define this playstyle.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Judgment Day passive is mandatory.</strong>
                    <p>This passive causes detonating marks to spread to nearby unmarked enemies. Combined with Seal of the Second Trumpet chains, this creates cascading explosions that clear entire screens. Without Judgment Day, the build loses its defining mechanic.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="tip-card">
                    <strong>Blessed Hammer is filler, not focus.</strong>
                    <p>Do not over-invest in Blessed Hammer damage. Its role is purely to maintain DPS during Judgment cooldowns. The real damage comes from Judgment detonations. Keep Blessed Hammer at 1/5 and focus on Judgment scaling.</p>
